    'ba37b1d2-4119-5c5d-8e7c-3b36a647a836'::uuid,
    'overhead_triceps_extension',
    'Overhead Triceps Extension',
    '{"merged_steps": ["**Overhead Triceps Extension with EZ Bar – Quick Guide** The **overhead position** *emphasizes the long head* of the triceps (because it''s stretched under load), the exercise **does engage all three triceps heads** (long, lateral, and medial) to some degree during extension.", "1.", "**Setup**: Sit on a bench (or stand) and hold an EZ bar with a narrow, overhand grip.", "Lift the bar overhead, arms fully extended.", "Keep your core tight and elbows close to your head.", "2.", "**Execution**: Slowly lower the bar behind your head by bending your elbows until they reach ~90°.", "Keep elbows pointed forward (not flaring out).", "3.", "**Finish**: Extend your arms back up to the starting position, squeezing your triceps at the top.", "**Tips**: * Control the movement to avoid straining your shoulders.", "* Use a moderate weight for full range of motion.", "* Keep your back straight and avoid arching."], "sources": [{"source": "wger", "file": "C:\\Users\\kaiqu\\Desktop\\SOMMA\\datasets\\wger-master\\wger\\exercises\\fixtures\\exercise-base-data.json", "steps": ["**Overhead Triceps Extension with EZ Bar – Quick Guide** The **overhead position** *emphasizes the long head* of the triceps (because it''s stretched under load), the exercise **does engage all three triceps heads** (long, lateral, and medial) to some degree during extension.", "1.", "**Setup**: Sit on a bench (or stand) and hold an EZ bar with a narrow, overhand grip.", "Lift the bar overhead, arms fully extended.", "Keep your core tight and elbows close to your head.", "2.", "**Execution**: Slowly lower the bar behind your head by bending your elbows until they reach ~90°.", "Keep elbows pointed forward (not flaring out).", "3.", "**Finish**: Extend your arms back up to the starting position, squeezing your triceps at the top.", "**Tips**: * Control the movement to avoid straining your shoulders.", "* Use a moderate weight for full range of motion.", "* Keep your back straight and avoid arching."], "description": "**Overhead Triceps Extension with EZ Bar – Quick Guide** The **overhead position** *emphasizes the long head* of the triceps (because it''s stretched under load), the exercise **does engage all three triceps heads** (long, lateral, and medial) to some degree during extension. 1. **Setup**: Sit on a bench (or stand) and hold an EZ bar with a narrow, overhand grip. Lift the bar overhead, arms fully extended. Keep your core tight and elbows close to your head. 2. **Execution**: Slowly lower the bar behind your head by bending your elbows until they reach ~90°. Keep elbows pointed forward (not flaring out). 3. **Finish**: Extend your arms back up to the starting position, squeezing your triceps at the top. **Tips**: * Control the movement to avoid straining your shoulders. * Use a moderate weight for full range of motion. * Keep your back straight and avoid arching."}], "summary": "**Overhead Triceps Extension with EZ Bar – Quick Guide** The **overhead position** *emphasizes the long head* of the triceps (because it''s stretched under load), the exercise **does engage all three triceps heads** (long, lateral, and medial) to some degree during extension. 1. **Setup**: Sit on a bench (or stand) and hold an EZ bar with a narrow, overhand grip. Lift the bar overhead, arms fully extended. Keep your core tight and elbows close to your head. 2. **Execution**: Slowly lower the bar behind your head by bending your elbows until they reach ~90°. Keep elbows pointed forward (not flaring out). 3. **Finish**: Extend your arms back up to the starting position, squeezing your triceps at the top. **Tips**: * Control the movement to avoid straining your shoulders. * Use a moderate weight for full range of motion. * Keep your back straight and avoid arching.", "setup": "**Overhead Triceps Extension with EZ Bar – Quick Guide** The **overhead position** *emphasizes the long head* of the triceps (because it''s stretched under load), the exercise **does engage all